description: Inomata’s Rice Washing Bowls are specially designed Japanese rice washing bowls for quickly washing or long soaking rice before cooking. A thorough cleansing in the Rice Washer can significantly reduce toxins and chemical levels incurred during the growing process. To soak rice, measure rice into the bowl with a solid bottom and cover with fresh water. Allow to soak for the instructed amount of time then rinse thoroughly. For cleaning rice quickly before cooking, use the Speed Washing Bowl with side and bottom drainers. Measure rice into the bowl and hold it under running tap water. Vigorously swish fingers through to loosen rice bran or starch, and allow husks and other particles to drain through the bottom and side. Continue until water runs clear. Both bowls are great for all types of rice, including brown rice, jasmine rice, even black, basmati, wild, white and short grain rice, sometimes called sticky rice due to its glue-like quality when cooked. Both Rice Washing Bowls work equally well as kitchen strainers for washing fruits and vegetables, legumes, barley and other larger grains. Made in Japan from food-grade plastic, The Rice Washing Bowls are BPA free and top-rack dishwasher safe for easy cleanup. Set includes 1 each Rice Washing Bowl (2-quart) for soaking and Rice Speed Washing Bowl (2.5-quart).

title: Organic Essiac Tea
description: Instructions for Preparation:1) Boil 1 gallon fresh spring water or distilled water in stainless steel pot. 2) Stir in 4 oz. of tea, cover pot.3) Boil 10 minutes.4) Remove from heat and stir. Cover and let sit for 12 hours at room temperature.5) Stir, cover, and bring to boil. Remove from heat.6) Strain through a fine mesh colander. Funnel liquid into clean amber glass bottle and cap. Tighten caps after cooling. Refrigerate. Mixture will stay fresh for 2-3 weeks if refrigerated. Directions for Use: 1) Shake herbal tea to mix well. Add 2 fl. oz. tea to equal amount (2 fl. oz.) boiled fresh spring water or distilled water. 2) Drink 2-4 fl. oz. daily on an empty stomach, preferably before bedtime. Important: Pregnant women consult your physician. Should use only stainless steel utensils when preparing this tea.Origin: United States
features: Ingredients: Organic burdock root, organic sheep sorrel herb, organic slippery elm bark, and organic (Turkey) rhubarb root. USDA Certified Organic CGMP Compliant (Current Good Manufacturing Practices)
